# New Service

## Arguments
- `name`: Service name (kebab-case, e.g., `billing-service`)
- `type`: `node-api` | `go-api` | `nextjs`
- `group`: Helm chart group (e.g., `core`, `domain`, `admin`)
- `features` (optional): Comma-separated features (e.g., `auth,cache,events,metrics`)

## Architecture

```
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}Node.js: @ironplate/service builder → Express + plugins → Helm chart → Tilt{{ end }}
{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}Go: envconfig + graceful + health packages → net/http → Helm chart → Tilt{{ end }}
```

## Steps

### 1. Create Service Files
- Create `apps/{name}/` with appropriate template files
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}
**Node.js API** — Use the `@ironplate/service` builder pattern:

```typescript
import { createService } from '@ironplate/service';
import { userRoutes } from './routes/users';

const service = await createService('{name}')
  .port(3001)
  .routes('/users', userRoutes)
  .build();

await service.start();
```

Key dependencies to add:
- `@ironplate/service` — Service builder framework (includes express, helmet, cors, compression, health checks)
- `@ironplate/config` — Zod-based environment config
- `@ironplate/logger` — Structured logging
- `@ironplate/errors` — Typed error classes
- `@ironplate/http-client` — Inter-service HTTP calls

Optional based on features:
- `@ironplate/auth` — JWT auth middleware (if `auth` feature)
- `@ironplate/cache` — Redis caching (if `cache` feature)
- `@ironplate/eventbus` — Dapr pub/sub (if `events` feature)
- `@ironplate/metrics` — Prometheus metrics (if `metrics` feature)
- `@ironplate/tracing` — OpenTelemetry (if `tracing` feature)
- `@ironplate/graphql` — Hasura client (if `graphql` feature)
- `@ironplate/validation` — Zod request validation
- `@ironplate/jobs` — Async job processing (if `jobs` feature)
{{ end }}{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}
**Go API** — Uses ironplate Go packages:

```go
import (
    "github.com/dag7/ironplate/packages/go/envconfig"
    "github.com/dag7/ironplate/packages/go/graceful"
    "github.com/dag7/ironplate/packages/go/health"
)
```

- `envconfig` for typed environment variable loading
- `graceful` for HTTP server with graceful shutdown
- `health` for Kubernetes-compatible health check handlers
{{ end }}

### 2. Create Helm Chart
- Create `k8s/helm/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/{group}/{name}/`
- `Chart.yaml` with `_lib/service` dependency
- `values.yaml` with service config (image, replicas, ports, env vars)
- `values.staging.yaml` and `values.production.yaml` for environment overrides
- Run `helm dependency update`

### 3. Update Tiltfile
- Add service entry in the `IRONPLATE:SERVICES:START/END` section
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}- For Node.js: `node_service(name='{name}', target=target)`
{{ end }}{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}- For Go: `go_service(name='{name}', target='debug', build_args={'TARGET_SRC_FOLDER': 'apps'})`
{{ end }}- Add `k8s_resource` with port forwards, resource deps, labels

### 4. Allocate Ports
- HTTP: next available from {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }} port range
- Debug: next available debug port
- Update `.ironplate/ports.json`

### 5. Post-Generation
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}- Run `{{ .Project.Spec.Monorepo.PackageManager }} install`{{ end }}
{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}- Update `go.work` and run `go mod tidy`{{ end }}
- Update `ironplate.yaml` services list

## CRITICAL Rules
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}- ALWAYS use `@ironplate/service` builder pattern for new Node.js services — never raw Express setup
- ALWAYS use `@ironplate/errors` for error types — never throw raw Error objects in API handlers
- ALWAYS add `@ironplate/health` routes (automatic with service builder)
- NEVER hardcode ports — use `@ironplate/config` with PORT env var{{ end }}
{{ if .Computed.HasGo }}- ALWAYS use `envconfig` package for config — never raw `os.Getenv`
- ALWAYS use `graceful.ListenAndServe` — never manual signal handling
- ALWAYS use `health.RegisterRoutes` — never inline health handlers{{ end }}

## Checklist
- [ ] Service source files created in `apps/{name}/`
- [ ] Uses `@ironplate/service` builder (Node) or ironplate Go packages (Go)
- [ ] Helm chart created with `_lib/service` dependency
- [ ] Environment-specific values files created
- [ ] Tiltfile updated with service entry
- [ ] Ports allocated and recorded
- [ ] Health endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`) working
- [ ] `tilt up` shows the new service
